Preconditions:
The input grid must not be null.
The input grid must have at least one row and one column.
The input grid must have an odd number of rows and columns.
The elements of the input grid must be integers.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer representing the maximum sum of the elements of an hourglass in the grid.
The method should not modify the input grid.
If there are multiple hourglasses with the same maximum sum, the method should return the sum of the first occurrence.
If the input grid is empty, the method should return 0.